  Scenario: Returning a CASE expression into pattern expression
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (a:A)
      CREATE (a)-[:T]->(:B),
             (a)-[:T]->(:C)
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (n)
      RETURN CASE
               WHEN id(n) >= 0 THEN (n)-->()
               ELSE 42
             END AS p
      """
    Then the result should be:
      | p                                      |
      | [<(:A)-[:T]->(:C)>, <(:A)-[:T]->(:B)>] |
      | []                                     |
      | []                                     |
    And no side effects

